<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="PIG02" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Arthur</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Pigott</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1749-10-19"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1819-09-06"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Lawyer</occupation><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Politician</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> See the first entry on 21 January 1793:  'Erskine and Pigot dismissed' : it is likely that this refers to Arthur Pigott <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">DNB</title> who was dismissed from the ofice of Solicitor General at the end of 1792, 
